This paper deals with the complexity of model-checking conjunctive queries on finite structures, which is a fundamental problem in database theory. Therefore, cs.DB (Databases) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also involves the use of data structures and algorithms for efficient enumeration, which suggests that it could also belong to cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms). The paper uses techniques from logic and combinatorics, which could place it in cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science). Additionally, the paper involves the study of fixed-parameter tractability, which could place it in cs.CC (Computational Complexity). Finally, the paper deals with the generalization of a result from a previous paper, which suggests that it could also belong to cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence).
